		"ItemTooltips"
		{
			"item_wind_lace"		"Additional mobility to keep up with enemy heroes"
			"item_meteor_hammer"		"The main problems you will face is keeping up in farm as the game goes and dealing with objectives. Meteor Hammer allowes you to farm efficiently and take towers, which in turn allowes you to use your early game dominance and stay relatively strong throughout the game.
ALTERNATIVE: Echo Sabre"
			"item_guardian_greaves"		"You want to make Greaves ASAP after Meteor - healing, mana sustain, armor, dispel. The only cases you&apos;d like to skip it are (a) when you&apos;re going for Hocket instead or (b) somebody else wants to make Greaves too and it will be better on the hero (e.g. Dazzle)"
			"item_holy_locket"		"An insanely powerful Undying item. Gives you great stats and makes Soul Rip much stronger"
			"item_rod_of_atos"		"A nice early item if you lack any kind of control on your team"
			"item_soul_ring"		"A nice item for early mana sustain, but usually Arcane Boots will be enough"
			"item_blade_mail"		"Armor solution, that also allowes you to farm even better and deal with focus in teamfights"
			"item_shivas_guard"		"Massive armor boost, regen reduction aura, additional mana and the slow to go with your ult"
			"item_octarine_core"		"Additional increase in power for Decay and Soul Rip - cooldown reduction, additional health (and spell lifesteal comes in handy, too)"
			"item_pipe"		"Casual Pipe for your team, good against magic heavy lineups"
			"item_lotus_orb"		"Good armor solution to get against roots/silences/other debuffs to help your team (or yourself if greaves is not enough). Usually would replace Shiva&apos;s (may also replace Greaves)"
			"item_heavens_halberd"		"Casual Halberd to help your team, Sange to increase your self healing"
			"item_arcane_boots"		"A good mana sustain item. Can be upgraded into Greaves later or disassembled into Holy Locket
ALTERNATIVE: Phase Boots"
			"item_phase_boots"		"ALTERNATIVE: Arcane Boots"
			"item_echo_sabre"		"ALTERNATIVE: Meteor Hammer"
			"item_black_king_bar"		"Better to get first against magic heavy lineups and slows/stuns"
